{{Infobox NRHP | name = Henry Gassaway Davis Mansion | nrhp_type = | image = HenryGlassawayDavisHouse2012.jpg | caption = | location= 15-17 Jones St. and 81 Second Street, [[Piedmont, West Virginia]] | coordinates = {{coord|39|28|55|N|79|2|59|W|display=inline,title}} | locmapin = Eastern Panhandle of West Virginia#West Virginia#USA | map_label = Henry Gassaway Davis House | built = 1871 | architect OR builder = Fredlock, E.J., Manufacturing Co. | architecture = Second Empire | added = December 19, 2008 | area = less than one acre | governing_body = Private | refnum = 08001239<ref name="nris">{{NRISref|version=2010a}}</ref> }} '''Henry Gassaway Davis House''', also known as the Knights of Pythias Lafayette Lodge Number 3 and Calanthe Temple #8 Pythian Sisters, is a historic home located at [[Piedmont, West Virginia|Piedmont]], [[Mineral County, West Virginia]]. It was built in 1871, for U.S. Senator and Vice Presidential nominee [[Henry G. Davis]] (1823-1916). It is a three bay, four story [[Second Empire architecture|Second Empire]] style brick duplex. It has a simple mansard roof and 12 gabled pedimented dormer windows on the concave slopes. The front façade features dual stone and slate stairs, ascending to two centered paired six by nine foot framed one-story entry porches.<ref name="dhr">{{cite web|url=http://www.wvculture.org/shpo/nr/pdf/mineral/08001239.pdf|title=National Register of Historic Places Inventory Nomination Form: Henry Gassaway Davis House|date=June 2007|accessdate=2011-08-18 |author=John T. Francis and Kelly Wilson|publisher=State of West Virginia, West Virginia Division of Culture and History, Historic Preservation}}</ref>
It was listed on the [[National Register of Historic Places]] in 2008.<ref name="nris"/>
