'''Thierry Ehrmann''' (born 1962) is the founder and current chairman of the Serveur Group,.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://serveur.com|title=Groupe Serveur -:- groupe Serveur/Server group :: Thierry Ehrmann|website=serveur.com}}</ref> He was born in [[Avignon, France|Avignon]]. He works from his house which has been transformed into the artwork [[Abode of Chaos]]. He's on the far left of the political French spectrum. He is a freemason, and had founded his own lodge (Faits et Documents, n° 117, 2001, p.&nbsp;1-2, 6).

== Serveur Group & Artprice.com ==
The Serveur Group manages [[database]]s of [[art auction]] quotations. The group has about 400 employees and annual revenue of about 70 million [[Euro]]s. The information is administered from the ArtPrice<ref name=artprice>{{cite web|url=http://artprice.com|title=Art market, auction sales and artist’s prices and indices - Artprice, the world leader of art market information.|first=Thierry|last=EHRMANN|website=artprice.com}}</ref> website, which is the legal and auctions interface to the group.

Artprice.com<ref name=artprice/> compiles and updates art reference databases that cover art auction prices, artist biographies and artworks images from its library of 290,000 auction catalogues. It is listed on Eurolist by [[Euronext Paris]] (ARTF/PRC). Artprice has been accused of using [[spamming|spam]] marketing campaigns.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.artbusiness.com/artpricecom.html|title=Artprice.com Uses "Decoy" Websites to Art Price Database|website=www.artbusiness.com}}</ref>

